A criminal gang has re-emerged in Athi River subcounty.Deputy county commissioner Geoffrey Omoding said the Usiku Sacco gang - a group of youths - has been terrorising residents.He addressed the press in his office last Friday. The gang members are armed with crude weapons and firearms. They operate from slums.&ldquo;We had dealt with the gang, but it seems they are regrouping. We will not allow them to harass, intimidate, harm or steal from Kenyans. Their days are numbered,&rdquo; Omoding said.The gang has been linked to a shootout at Ngei Two Estate in Athi River town last Wednesday night. The thugs escaped after robbing a woman.Police recovered cartridges. Omoding urged residents to cooperate with security agencies to eliminate the gang. He told parents their children can be rehabilitated.